# Data Directory

## Paderborn University Bearing Dataset

### Download Instructions

1. Visit the official dataset page:  
   https://mb.uni-paderborn.de/kat/forschung/kat-datacenter/bearing-datacenter/

2. Download `paderborn-db.zip`

3. Place the file here: `data/paderborn-db.zip`

### Dataset Structure

The dataset contains vibration signals from bearings under different health conditions:

| Label | Folders | Description |
|-------|---------|-------------|
| Healthy | K001–K006 | Normal operating bearings |
| Inner fault | KI04, KI14, KI16 | Inner race damage |
| Outer fault | KA04, KA15, KA16 | Outer race damage |
| Mixed fault | KB23 | Combined damage |

### Sampling Details

- Original sampling rate: 64,000 Hz
- Resampled to: 12,000 Hz
- FFT window size: 1024 samples
- Hop size: 256 samples
- FFT bins (features): 513

### Notes

- Raw `.zip` and `.mat` files are excluded from version control via `.gitignore`
- All preprocessing is done on-the-fly in `src/data_loader.py`
- No manual extraction needed — the pipeline reads directly from the `.zip`
